# Content & Tests Guide

> Applies to every CEFR level. The shared test templates, scoring component
> and quality rules apply 1:1 to A1, A2, B1, B2.

## Test vs Lesson — Key Differences

Tests have **3 files only** (no `content.ts`, no `workbook.ts`):

```
src/content/<level>/tests/<test-folder>/
  ├── metadata.ts     — id, number, afterLesson, title, totalPoints, introText
  ├── exercises.ts    — ALL exercises grouped by section (listening, reading, grammar, writing)
  └── index.ts        — assembles TestData with sections array
```

After creating the files, register the test **in the level's index file**
(e.g. `src/content/a2/index.ts`):
- Add a loader to `<LEVEL>_TEST_LOADERS`
- Add an entry to `<LEVEL>_TEST_FOLDER_MAP` (testId → folder name on disk)
- Add an entry to `<LEVEL>_TEST_NEXT_LESSON_MAP` (testId → next lesson id)
- Verify the `<LEVEL>_NAV_ITEMS` has the correct `label` for the sidebar

## ID Naming Conventions

| Element | Format | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Test | `test-a1-N` | `test-a1-1` |
| Listening | `t0N-sl-xxx` | `t01-sl-text`, `t01-sl-tf` |
| Reading | `t0N-ch-xxx` | `t01-ch-text`, `t01-ch-fill` |
| Grammar | `t0N-gr-N` | `t01-gr-1`, `t01-gr-2` |
| Writing | `t0N-pi-xxx` | `t01-pi-spell` |

## Asset Paths

Assets go in `/public/assets/<test-id>/` (folder name = test ID — e.g.
`/public/assets/test-a1-3/` or `/public/assets/test-a2-1/`) with subfolders:
- `slushane/` — listening section images (speaker photos)
- `chetene/` — reading section images (dialog photos, context images)
- `gramatika/` — grammar section context images (decorative, shown above exercise)
- `pisane/` — writing section images (individual food items OR shared basket/scene)

Source files on developer machine:
`C:\Users\Work Account\Desktop\CURSOR\a1-files\lessons\test-lessons-X-Y\` (A1)
or the equivalent A2/B1/B2 source folders.

## Test Structure — 4 Sections

Every test has exactly 4 sections in this order:

| Section | ID | Section `name` (sidebar) | Typical types |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1. Слушане | `listening` | `КОМПОНЕНТ СЛУШАНЕ` | `reading_text` (hidden) + `true_false` |
| 2. Четене | `reading` | `КОМПОНЕНТ ЧЕТЕНЕ` | `reading_text` (no translate) + `workbook_fill_blank` |
| 3. Граматика | `grammar` | `КОМПОНЕНТ ГРАМАТИКА` | `workbook_fill_blank`, `word_order`, `multiple_choice` |
| 4. Писане | `writing` | `КОМПОНЕНТ ПИСАНЕ` | `syllable_blocks` (with per-puzzle images) |

Section ГОВОРЕНЕ is excluded from digital tests.

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Exercise `title` vs. Section `name`

Two different fields, often confused:

| Field | Example value | Where shown |
|---|---|---|
| **Section `name`** (in `index.ts`) | `'КОМПОНЕНТ СЛУШАНЕ'` | Sidebar / navigation — allowed to keep the „КОМПОНЕНТ" format as a section heading |
| **Exercise `title`** (per exercise in `exercises.ts`) | `'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 1'`, `'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 2'`... | Card header on the exercise page — MUST be „УПРАЖНЕНИЕ N" |

**Never** set an exercise's `title` to „КОМПОНЕНТ СЛУШАНЕ" / „КОМПОНЕНТ ЧЕТЕНЕ" / „КОМПОНЕНТ ГРАМАТИКА" / „КОМПОНЕНТ ПИСАНЕ". Those are PDF labels; in the digital test the section name is shown separately in the sidebar and every exercise inside a section is numbered „УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 1" → „УПРАЖНЕНИЕ N" counting from the first exercise in THAT section.

Example per section:

```ts
// listening exercises:
{ id: 't01-sl-text', type: 'reading_text', title: 'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 1', ... }
{ id: 't01-sl-tf',   type: 'true_false',   title: 'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 2', ... }

// reading exercises (numbering restarts within section):
{ id: 't01-ch-text', type: 'reading_text',        title: 'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 1', ... }
{ id: 't01-ch-fill', type: 'workbook_fill_blank', title: 'УПРАЖНЕНИЕ 2', ... }
```

